{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Exempt Electric Vehicles with an RRP up to \u00a360,000 from Expensive Car Supplement",
        "additional_details": "The current \u00a350,000 threshold still captures many essential family-sized EVs, effectively penalising drivers for making a sustainable choice. Increasing this to \u00a360,000 would better reflect the current market prices of long-range electric vehicles and further incentivise the transition to net-zero by making cleaner transport more affordable",
        "background": "Call on the Government to raise the list price threshold for the Vehicle Excise Duty (VED) \"Expensive Car Supplement\" (Luxury Road Tax) for zero-emission vehicles from the current limit to \u00a360,000 for all such vehicles manufactured from April 2025 onwards",
